# 🚀 K8s Replicator v{{VERSION_TAG}}

Welcome to K8s Replicator v{{VERSION_TAG}}! 🎉 This release brings exciting new features, improvements, and bugfixes.

## 📖 How to Use

Check the [README](https://github.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/tree/{{VERSION_TAG}}#quick-start-) for quick start instructions and the [Documentation](https://github.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/tree/{{VERSION_TAG}}#documentation-) for comprehensive guides.

## 🔧 Installation

```bash
curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/main/installers/install.sh | bash -s {{VERSION_TAG}}
```

## 📝 Changelog

### ✨ New Features
- **Role Replication**: Added support for replicating Kubernetes Roles across namespaces
- **RoleBinding Replication**: Added support for replicating Kubernetes RoleBindings across namespaces  
- **ServiceAccount Replication**: Added support for replicating Kubernetes ServiceAccounts across namespaces

### 🐛 Bugfixes
- Fixed minor pipeline environment variable usages
- Fixed GitHub superlinter issues

### 🔧 Improvements
- Moved kubebuilder annotations to individual replicator files for better organization
- Refactored controller structure and moved to root directory
- Improved codebase organization and structure
- Enhanced workflow permissions and security
- Upgraded GoLang version to 1.24.6
- Upgraded operator framework to v1.37.0
- Switched from CodeQL to Trivy for security scanning
- Improved build workflows and CI/CD processes

### 📚 Documentation
- Added comprehensive AGENTS.md file for AI assistant navigation
- Added detailed API.md with complete API reference
- Added ARCHITECTURE.md with technical architecture details
- Added CONTRIBUTING.md with development setup and workflow
- Added TROUBLESHOOTING.md for common issues and debugging
- Added SECURITY.md for security policies
- Added ADOPTERS.md for project adoption tracking
- Added CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md for community guidelines
- Enhanced examples documentation with cert-manager use case
- Moved replicator interface documentation to GoLang doc strings
- Added more commit types to contribution guide
- Improved README.md structure and content

### 🔒 Security
- Enhanced workflow permissions
- Switched to Trivy for security scanning
- Pinned security action dependencies
- Improved RBAC configuration for new resource types

## 🏗️ Architecture

K8s Replicator is built with an extensible architecture. See the [Supported Resources](https://github.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/blob/{{VERSION_TAG}}/API.md#supported-resources) section in our API documentation for currently supported resource types.

Need support for a different resource type? Check out our [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/blob/{{VERSION_TAG}}/CONTRIBUTING.md#extending-the-operator) for implementation instructions! 🚀

## 🤝 Contributing

We welcome contributions! See our [Contributing Guide](https://github.com/nadundesilva/k8s-replicator/blob/{{VERSION_TAG}}/CONTRIBUTING.md) for development setup and workflow.

